metadata.metaValue: We want to use an other prototype for the leaves so we first remove the current prototypes relationship from the PointInstancer.

We create a new prim called *prototypes* bellow the PointInstancer just to make it more obvious than in the original PointInstancer.
We then add a new mesh bellow the *prototypes* prim.
We tell the PointInstancer that our new *prototypes/<mesh_name>* prim will be the new prototype (used as a leaf :) )
